      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk i feel like you're dismissing that perspective pretty quickly. if the research isn't supporting it, why do so many economists still argue that the \"welfare trap\" is a real thing? it seems like you're saying the benefits are clearly a good thing and almost always help, but isn't that a bit one-sided? isn't there any actual data that shows the negative impact of these benefits on the incentive to work?",
